Looking at this theorem, I need to prove that `δ_ε_correlatedAgreementAffineLines` holds for Reed-Solomon codes in the unique decoding regime.

The key insight is that this is a special case of the more general proximity gap theorem `proximity_gap_RSCodes`. The hypothesis `hδ : δ ≤ relativeUniqueDecodingRadius` implies that `δ` is in the unique decoding regime, which means `δ ≤ (1-ρ)/2`. 

Since `relativeUniqueDecodingRadius ≤ (1-ρ)/2 ≤ 1 - sqrt(ρ)`, we can apply the proximity gap theorem. The correlated agreement property for affine lines should follow from the proximity gap property when restricted to 1-dimensional affine spaces (lines).

```lean
theorem RS_correlatedAgreement_affineLines_uniqueDecodingRegime
    {deg : ℕ} {domain : ι ↪ F} {δ : ℝ≥0}
    (hδ : δ ≤ relativeUniqueDecodingRadius (ι := ι) (F := F) (C := ReedSolomon.code domain deg))
    : δ_ε_correlatedAgreementAffineLines (A := F) (F := F) (ι := ι)
    (C := ReedSolomon.code domain deg) (δ := δ) (ε := errorBound δ deg domain) := by
  apply correlatedAgreement_of_proximityGap
  apply proximity_gap_RSCodes
  calc δ ≤ relativeUniqueDecodingRadius (ReedSolomon.code domain deg) := hδ
       _ ≤ 1 - (ReedSolomonCode.sqrtRate deg domain) := relativeUniqueDecodingRadius_le_Johnson
```
